	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Repro steps:&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game (not as a Drow).&#xD;&#xA;2. loadlevel WLD_Main_A&#xD;&#xA;3. goto 298.109; 36.973; -16&#xD;&#xA;4. Talk to Priestess Gut &gt; accept the brand &gt; accept her help with the tadpole &gt; follow her &gt; talk to her again and say yes.&#xD;&#xA;5. Let her rummage into your brain &gt; tell her to get it out &gt; i'm ready.&#xD;&#xA;6. Drink the potion." />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="215" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="Players wake from a sleeping spell/potion to find themselves chained, captive, in a cellar. The last thing they remember is accepting help from the goblin priestess, who has now captured them. She is sadistic and takes great pleasure in explaining that they're going to become mindflayers due to the parasite in their head, and that she's going to keep them trapped here until that happens.&#xD;&#xA;Barbarian characters can break free at the end if they succeed a strength check. Combat with Gut ensues." />
